    <briefdescription>
<para>A struct representing a single discrete option in a list for a setting. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>A struct representing a single discrete option in a list for a setting (e.g. &quot;High&quot;, &quot;1920x1080&quot;, &quot;Monitor 1&quot;), with a localized display name and an associated value object of the abstract type <ref refid="classUSFSettingValue" kindref="compound">USFSettingValue</ref>. This allows for great flexibility in defining what each option represents and how it behaves when selected.</para>
<para>This struct is used as the value for <ref refid="classUSFSettingDefinition__Discrete" kindref="compound">USFSettingDefinition_Discrete</ref>. <simplesect kind="note"><para><computeroutput>BlueprintType</computeroutput> </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
